This patch changes WITH_LIBXML from dynamic (the upstream default, `WITH_LIBXML=1`)
to static (`WITH_LIBXML=static`), and WITH_TIDY from dynamic (`WITH_TIDY=1`) to
static (`WITH_TIDY=static`). This is the Session 5 surgical linking fix.

Background (see DECISIONS.md ADR-0014):
Session 4 was blocked by the following init-path failure in workerd:
  receiveInstance → loadDylibs → reportUndefinedSymbols → addFunction
  → convertJsFunctionToWasm → new WebAssembly.Module(bytes) → BLOCKED

The root cause is that WITH_LIBXML=dynamic (the upstream default) leaves four
libxml2 symbols undefined in the main wasm binary's GOT:
  xmlStrdup, xmlStrncmp, xmlURIUnescapeString, xmlUnlinkNode

These are referenced by ext/libxml MINIT → xmlInitParser(), which fires during
php_embed_init('embed'). In dynamic mode, libxml2 is a WASM side module
(DYNAMIC_LIBS_GROUPED+= xml-libs, LIBXML_DYNAMIC_LOAD=1). The symbols are
expected to come from the side module at runtime, not from the main binary.

In workerd, the stub-creation path (addFunction → convertJsFunctionToWasm) is
blocked because workerd disallows runtime WebAssembly.Module() compilation and
lacks WebAssembly.Function. No JS-level workaround is possible.

Fix: WITH_LIBXML=static adds lib/lib/libxml2.a to ARCHIVES (statically linked into
the main binary) and does NOT add xml-libs to DYNAMIC_LIBS_GROUPED. The four
undefined symbols are resolved at link time. reportUndefinedSymbols finds nothing
undefined in the GOT → addFunction is never called → no blocked wasm compilation.

WITH_TIDY=static is required because WITH_TIDY=dynamic requires WITH_LIBXML=dynamic
(enforced by php-wasm-tidy/static.mak). Changing to static links libtidy.a into
the main binary as well.

Changes vs. the upstream baseline (on top of sessions 2, 3, iconv-resolution):
- WITH_LIBXML=1 → WITH_LIBXML=static in .circleci/.env_8.0.ci
- WITH_TIDY=1  → WITH_TIDY=static  in .circleci/.env_8.0.ci
- WITH_ICONV=1 → WITH_ICONV=0 (iconv-resolution patch, already applied)

Apply order:
  1. patches/session2-fp_async_call.patch
  2. patches/session3-suspend.patch
  3. patches/iconv-resolution.patch
  4. patches/session5-static-libxml.patch  ← this file (git apply from upstream root)

--- a/.circleci/.env_8.0.ci
+++ b/.circleci/.env_8.0.ci
@@ -14,13 +14,13 @@ WITH_MBSTRING=1
 WITH_PHAR=1
 WITH_TOKENIZER=1

-WITH_LIBXML=1
+WITH_LIBXML=static
 WITH_DOM=1
 WITH_XML=1
 WITH_SIMPLEXML=1

 WITH_LIBZIP=1
-WITH_ICONV=1
+WITH_ICONV=0
 WITH_SQLITE=1

@@ -39,7 +39,7 @@ WITH_GD=1
 WITH_ZLIB=1

-WITH_TIDY=1
+WITH_TIDY=static

Note: the WITH_ICONV=0 line above belongs to the iconv-resolution patch
(already applied in the upstream checkout). It appears here only because
both patches modify the same file.

Both libxml2.a and libtidy.a must be pre-built (from a prior docker make run)
before this rebuild. They are preserved in the Docker build cache under
~/scratch/php-wasm-upstream/lib/lib/.
